                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#1r" facs="002">Fol. 1r</locus><desc>Line drawing of Walatta Ṗeṭros and the Lord with caption<q>How our Lord gave a covenant to Walatta Ṗeṭros, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ ወሐባ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ለወለተ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ እግዚአነ።</foreign></q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#120v" facs="121">Fol. 120v</locus><desc><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>(?), Walatta Ṗeṭros(?) and the Lord, two patrons prostrate beneath</desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#139v #140r #140v" facs="140 141">Fols. 139v, 140r, 140v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The Chronology of Walatta Ṗeṭros and the subsequent community, written in a different hand.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#141v" facs="142">Fol. 141v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (written upside down): Additional miracle of Walatta Ṗeṭros, written in a different hand.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#142r" facs="142">Fol. 142r</locus>
                    <desc type="Record">
                    Record: land grant in the reign of ʾaḍe Takla Giyorgis (I, whose dates are 1779-1784, 1788-1789, 1794-1795, 1795-1796, 1798-1799, 1800; or II whose dates are 1869‒1871) written in a bold, different hand.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    Digitized by Wendy Laura Belcher with Selamawit Mecca in January 2011 with a Canon Powershot outdoors at the Qʷaraṭa Walatta Ṗeṭros Monastery on the east shore of lake Ṭānā
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#1v" facs="002">Fol. 1v</locus>
                    <desc type="Record">
                    Record of land inheritance
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#84v" facs="085">Fol. 84v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    mostly blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#119r" facs="119">Fol. 119r</locus>
                    <desc>
                      mentions the abess of the community, <foreign xml:lang="gez">አመተ፡ ድንግል፡</foreign>, ʾAmata Dǝngǝl, and the abott, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘሐዋርያት፡ አመተ፡ ድንግል፡ ዘሐዋርያት፡ ሰላም፡ ለኪ፡ ወለተ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ገነት፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <locus target="#121r" facs="121">Fol. 121r</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      an owner or patron is mentioned, <foreign xml:lang="gez">አክሮስያ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <locus target="#139r" facs="139">Fol. 139r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Record: land transaction, mentioning the Abess and the women leaders of the community
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#Inside back cover" facs="144">Fols. Inside,, </locus>
                    <q>
                    IV 721
                    </q>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                      <material key="leather"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin>
                     According to Wendy Belcher, this manuscript is the autograph of the  <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1509GadlaW">Gadla Walatta
                                                  Ṗeṭros</ref>, written in
                     <origDate when="1672"/>. Should this not be the case, it was written before <origDate notAfter="1681">1681</origDate>.
                     Digitised in <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5286Qwarac">Qwäraḉa</placeName> in 2011.
                  </origin>
               </history>
